text: South Cliffe is a village in the East Riding of Yorkshire, England. It is situated about north of North Cave, west of Newbald and about south of Market Weighton. It bestrides Cliffe Road. Parish Church of St John, serving North Cliffe and South Cliffe Together with North Cliffe it forms the civil parish of North and South Cliffe. ==References== * ==External links== * * Category:Villages in the East Riding of Yorkshire
